--------------------------------------------------------------------------------SOA------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-Service oriented architecture
-App makes use of services avaliable over the network.
-MAKEMYTRIP,AMAZON
-SOAP and REST

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------SOAP-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-Simple Object Access Protocol
-Any protocol
-Have XML data format
-Different operations

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------REST----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-Representational state transfer.
-CREATE: http->post->http://host:port/emp
  GET: http://host:port/emp ->retrieve
  DELETE -> delete
  PUT->update
-HTTP headers: get->retrival
               post->create
               put->update
               delete->remove

-Rich client: junit
-Thin client: UI testing, user interaction
-REST API: postman

-Emp, EmpManager(CRUD), UI Code -> accept emp
call add of empmanager()
  C: length of data added to list
  R: check inserted data
  U: check for modification
  D: remove code
  
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------JUNIT-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 -unit testing framework for Java.
 -first testing then coding
 -have different annotations : @beforetest, @aftertest,@test
 -TDD: test driven development for unit testing and integration testing
 -BDD: behaviour dirven development follows scripts in plian text.
